In this tutorial, youll learn how to deploy a Next.js application to Vercel while integrating it with a Java web service backend. Well walk you through setting up a Next.js app, configuring API routes, and deploying it to Vercel for easy hosting and continuous integration. Additionally, youll learn how to connect the frontend with a Java-based web service, handling API requests and ensuring smooth communication between the two. By the end of this tutorial, you'll have a fully deployed, full-stack application with a modern frontend on Vercel and a robust Java backend, ready for production. Whether youre new to Vercel, Next.js, or Java, this guide will give you the practical knowledge to deploy and scale your web applications with ease.

title.en-US: Deploying a NextJS app to vercel

content.value: In this tutorial, you'll learn how to build a Python Flask backend that serves a simple React frontend. Well walk you through setting up a Flask API to handle data requests and serve your React app as a static file. You'll learn how to configure Flask to work with a React development environment, manage API routes, and ensure smooth communication between the frontend and backend. By the end of the tutorial, you'll have a basic full-stack app that demonstrates the integration of Flask with React, providing you with the foundational skills to build more complex web applications. This is a perfect starting point for anyone looking to combine the simplicity of Flask with the power of React.

title.en-US: Full stack Python React queue app

content.value: In this tutorial, you'll learn how to refactor and optimize enterprise applications with zero downtime, ensuring a seamless user experience during updates and performance improvements. Well walk you through strategies like blue-green deployments, canary releases, and rolling updates to manage application upgrades without service interruptions. Youll explore best practices for improving code efficiency, reducing technical debt, and implementing automated testing and monitoring to catch issues early. By the end, you'll understand how to apply these techniques to maintain high availability while enhancing performance, scalability, and maintainability in large-scale applications. Whether youre working with monolithic systems or microservices, this guide will equip you with the tools and knowledge to optimize enterprise applications with minimal risk and maximum uptime.

In this tutorial, youll learn how to deploy a Java-based web service using AWS serverless technologies, including AWS Lambda, API Gateway, and DynamoDB. Well guide you through the process of setting up your Java application in a serverless environment, where youll write, package, and deploy your code to AWS Lambda with minimal infrastructure management. Youll also configure API Gateway to handle HTTP requests and integrate with a DynamoDB database to store and retrieve data. By the end of this tutorial, you'll have a fully deployed, scalable Java web service running in the cloud, with reduced operational overhead and the flexibility to scale automatically based on demand. Whether you're new to AWS or just looking to explore serverless architecture, this step-by-step guide will help you build and deploy an efficient Java web service without the need for managing traditional servers.

In this tutorial, you'll learn how to write and run integration tests for your web applications using Cypress, a powerful and easy-to-use testing framework. We'll start by setting up Cypress in your project and exploring its intuitive interface for writing tests. You'll learn how to simulate user interactions like clicking buttons, filling out forms, and navigating between pages to test the integration of different components within your app. As we dive deeper, you'll also cover best practices for structuring your tests, handling asynchronous code, and managing test data. By the end of the tutorial, you'll be confident in using Cypress to automate and validate end-to-end workflows, ensuring your web application behaves as expected in real-world scenarios. Whether you're new to testing or looking to add integration testing to your workflow, this guide will help you get started with writing reliable tests that improve your apps quality.

title.en-US: Increase code confidence and catch bugs with cypress

content.value: In this tutorial, you'll compare deploying two popular web frameworksPython Flask and Ruby on Railson an AWS EC2 instance. Well walk you through the process of setting up an EC2 instance, configuring the environment, and deploying a simple application using Flask and Ruby on Rails. Along the way, you'll learn key differences in setup, performance, and deployment workflows for each framework, helping you understand the trade-offs between Python and Ruby in a cloud environment. Youll also explore best practices for managing dependencies, setting up databases, and securing your EC2 instance. By the end of the tutorial, youll have a deeper understanding of how to deploy both frameworks on EC2 and be able to choose the best option for your specific project needs. Whether you're deciding which framework to use or just looking to learn the deployment process, this guide provides a clear, hands-on comparison.

title.en-US: EC2 Deployment Battle: Python Flask vs. Ruby on Rails

Well start by exploring the basics of setting up and configuring a server, followed by deploying a simple web service using popular technologies like Python Flask, Node.js, or Java Spring Boot. Youll gain hands-on experience with cloud platforms such as AWS, Google Cloud, or Azure, and learn how to deploy your service using virtual machines, containers, or serverless architectures. Along the way, well cover critical topics like database integration, scaling, load balancing, and securing your web service with SSL certificates and firewalls. By the end of the tutorial, you'll be equipped with the knowledge to deploy web services reliably and efficiently, whether youre building a small app or scaling to handle millions of users. Whether you're new to deployment or looking to refine your skills, this guide will help you navigate the challenges and streamline your web service deployment process.

This comprehensive DevOps learning path takes you from traditional deployment methods to modern, scalable infrastructure practices. You'll start by containerizing applications with Docker, learning how to package and distribute your code consistently across environments. From there, you'll dive into Kubernetes for orchestration, discovering how to manage, scale, and monitor containerized applications in production. The path progresses through essential DevOps practices including CI/CD pipelines, infrastructure as code, and monitoring strategies. Finally, you'll explore cloud-native architectures and learn how to implement robust, automated deployment workflows that can handle enterprise-scale applications. Whether you're transitioning from manual deployments or looking to modernize your infrastructure skills, this path will give you the expertise to build and maintain production-ready systems.

subtitle.en-US: Master modern deployment with containers, orchestration, and cloud-native practices

content.value: Master the fundamentals of Docker containerization in this comprehensive tutorial. You'll start by understanding what containers are and why they've revolutionized application deployment. We'll guide you through installing Docker, creating your first Dockerfile, and building container images from scratch. You'll learn essential Docker commands for managing containers, images, and volumes, plus best practices for writing efficient Dockerfiles. The tutorial covers multi-stage builds for optimizing image size, working with Docker networks, and using Docker Compose for multi-container applications. You'll also explore container security basics, debugging techniques, and strategies for managing persistent data. By the end, you'll be confident containerizing any application and understand how Docker fits into modern DevOps workflows. Whether you're new to containers or looking to solidify your Docker knowledge, this hands-on tutorial provides the foundation you need to succeed.

Dive deep into Kubernetes orchestration and learn how to manage containerized applications at scale. This comprehensive tutorial starts with Kubernetes architecture fundamentals, explaining pods, nodes, and clusters. You'll get hands-on experience creating and managing pods, services, and deployments using both kubectl commands and YAML manifests. We'll cover essential concepts like ReplicaSets, ConfigMaps, and Secrets for managing application configuration and sensitive data. You'll learn about different service types (ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer) and how to expose applications effectively. The tutorial also covers advanced topics including horizontal pod autoscaling, rolling updates, resource management, and health checks. You'll explore ingress controllers for routing external traffic and persistent volumes for stateful applications. By the end, you'll understand how to deploy, scale, and maintain robust applications in Kubernetes, making you ready to handle production workloads with confidence.

Build robust CI/CD pipelines that automate your entire software delivery process from code commit to production deployment. This tutorial covers continuous integration and continuous deployment fundamentals, starting with version control best practices and branching strategies. You'll learn to set up automated builds, run comprehensive test suites, and implement quality gates that ensure only high-quality code reaches production. We'll explore popular CI/CD platforms like GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, Jenkins, and Azure DevOps, showing you how to configure pipelines for different programming languages and frameworks. The tutorial covers advanced concepts including parallel execution, artifact management, environment promotion strategies, and rollback mechanisms. You'll also learn about security scanning, dependency management, and monitoring pipeline performance. By the end, you'll be able to design and implement CI/CD pipelines that reduce deployment risk, increase development velocity, and ensure consistent, reliable software releases across your organization.

Transform your infrastructure management with Infrastructure as Code (IaC) principles and tools. This comprehensive tutorial introduces you to the concept of treating infrastructure like software, enabling version control, testing, and automation of your cloud resources. You'll start with Terraform fundamentals, learning to write declarative configuration files that define your infrastructure state. We'll cover essential concepts like providers, resources, variables, and modules, plus advanced features like remote state management and workspace organization. The tutorial also explores AWS CloudFormation for AWS-specific deployments, showing you how to create and manage stacks efficiently. You'll learn best practices for organizing IaC projects, implementing testing strategies, and handling secrets securely. We'll cover multi-environment deployments, infrastructure versioning, and disaster recovery scenarios. By the end, you'll be able to provision, modify, and destroy infrastructure reliably using code, making your infrastructure more predictable, scalable, and maintainable than traditional manual approaches.

Master monitoring and observability to gain deep insights into your applications and infrastructure performance. This tutorial covers the three pillars of observability: metrics, logs, and traces, showing you how to implement comprehensive monitoring strategies. You'll learn to set up monitoring tools like Prometheus, Grafana, and the ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana) to collect, store, and visualize system data. We'll explore application performance monitoring (APM) with tools like Jaeger for distributed tracing and understand how to track requests across microservices. The tutorial covers alerting best practices, including defining meaningful SLIs and SLOs, creating effective alert rules, and avoiding alert fatigue. You'll learn log aggregation strategies, structured logging, and how to correlate events across systems. We'll also cover infrastructure monitoring, custom metrics creation, and capacity planning techniques. By the end, you'll be able to implement robust observability solutions that help you proactively identify issues, optimize performance, and maintain high system reliability.
Heading 2

Dive into the fundamentals of machine learning with Python in this comprehensive beginner's guide. You'll start by understanding key ML concepts like supervised and unsupervised learning, then explore popular libraries including scikit-learn, pandas, and NumPy. Through hands-on exercises, you'll build your first classification and regression models, learn data preprocessing techniques, and understand model evaluation metrics. We'll cover essential topics like feature engineering, cross-validation, and avoiding overfitting. By the end of this tutorial, you'll have built several real-world ML models and gained the confidence to tackle more advanced machine learning projects. Perfect for developers transitioning into data science or anyone curious about AI fundamentals.
